metadata.name: Divide
metadata.description:
When the energy of two waves reflects and refracts, moments like 'Divide' are created. 

One does not accidentally capture an image like this.

Sometimes years are spent chasing one fraction of a second. Travelling, searching, carrying bulky bags of camera equipment on and off planes, boats and helicopters, years of swimming with a camera in a waterproof housing - to seek out these moments of ephemerality.

Oce captured, this singular moment is then transformed into a mesmerizing moving image, detailing the oceanâ€™s myriad of colours and textures, as well as its immense power.
